WEBVTT

00:00:05.060 --> 00:00:08.110
Yeah! Trainer's taking 
me out tomorrow morning,

00:00:08.110 --> 00:00:10.460
and I wondered if you wanted to come along.

00:00:11.630 --> 00:00:15.640
Thank you for asking. I believe 
I'll take you up on that offer.

00:00:15.640 --> 00:00:18.140
Great! I'll be waiting tomorrow, then.

00:00:18.380 --> 00:00:20.140
Right. See you then.

00:00:20.140 --> 00:00:21.890
Yeah! Goodnight.

00:00:26.020 --> 00:00:30.020
Teio... I will strive to remain the strongest,

00:00:30.020 --> 00:00:34.070
in anticipation of the day you return.

00:00:35.820 --> 00:00:37.940
I won't lose, no matter what.

00:01:02.520 --> 00:01:09.730
Umamusume

00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.730
Pretty Derby

00:02:16.780 --> 00:02:21.740
{\an1}Episode 12
 Together

00:02:17.710 --> 00:02:20.760
This is harder than I thought!

00:02:20.760 --> 00:02:23.770
Beach sand is softer and more 
granular than what we're used to.

00:02:23.770 --> 00:02:26.400
If you step forward normally, you generate

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:28.890
an insufficient amount of propulsive force.

00:02:28.890 --> 00:02:31.040
And, uh, that means?

00:02:31.040 --> 00:02:35.150
It means you need to make sure your form is 
correct if you want to move effectively.

00:02:35.420 --> 00:02:38.140
It's quite effective training, actually.

00:02:38.140 --> 00:02:39.650
I see...

00:02:39.650 --> 00:02:41.720
Okay, in that case!

00:02:57.180 --> 00:02:59.300
Goal!

00:03:01.930 --> 00:03:03.680
Nice work, you two.

00:03:03.680 --> 00:03:05.430
Have some hydration.

00:03:05.430 --> 00:03:07.440
Thanks, Trainer!

00:03:07.440 --> 00:03:08.930
Much obliged.

00:03:11.440 --> 00:03:14.630
You don't have to match my pace, y'know.

00:03:14.630 --> 00:03:15.190
Excuse me?

00:03:15.190 --> 00:03:18.290
You could've gone faster, right, McQueen?

00:03:19.080 --> 00:03:20.360
Well, yes.

00:03:23.200 --> 00:03:28.420
Trainer-san, would it be all right if I did
a bit of independent training for a while?

00:03:28.420 --> 00:03:29.450
On your own?

00:03:29.450 --> 00:03:34.460
Yes. There are a few things I've been
 considering, moving into the Fall Tennoushou.

00:03:34.670 --> 00:03:37.880
I'm not gonna say no to 
you of all horse girls.

00:03:37.880 --> 00:03:40.710
That said, call me if you 
need any help, all right?

00:03:40.710 --> 00:03:42.270
Thank you.

00:03:42.270 --> 00:03:44.340
What are you going to do 
for your solo training?

00:03:44.340 --> 00:03:47.850
Well, I was thinking of 
adding pool exercises.

00:03:47.850 --> 00:03:48.850
In that case...

00:03:49.070 --> 00:03:51.100
Let's go for a swim while we're here!

00:03:51.100 --> 00:03:53.350
But it's already November.

00:03:53.350 --> 00:03:54.350
It's fine!

00:03:54.350 --> 00:03:56.010
It won't be so bad!

00:03:56.010 --> 00:03:57.990
See, it's not that...

00:03:57.990 --> 00:03:59.480
So cold!

00:03:59.480 --> 00:04:00.990
I was trying to warn you...

00:04:01.790 --> 00:04:03.860
Teio, please, stop that!

00:04:02.370 --> 00:04:05.950
Seriously, it's fine! 
Once you get in, you'll feel fine!

00:04:06.380 --> 00:04:07.380
Whoo!

00:04:07.380 --> 00:04:08.330
Whoo!

00:04:08.330 --> 00:04:11.700
Time to have Fukukitaru-san 
check out my fortune again!

00:04:11.700 --> 00:04:12.200
Yo!

00:04:12.490 --> 00:04:14.700
Fukukitaru-san, we're back!

00:04:15.940 --> 00:04:17.590
Huh? She's gone?

00:04:18.420 --> 00:04:19.390
Is this a note?

00:04:20.120 --> 00:04:21.960
"Dear Mejiro Palmer-chan..."

00:04:21.960 --> 00:04:27.330
"If you are reading this note, 
I have abandoned this location."

00:04:28.320 --> 00:04:31.220
You no longer require the 
guidance of my fortunes.

00:04:31.220 --> 00:04:33.890
You are already a splendid, 
outrunning horse girl!

00:04:33.890 --> 00:04:37.540
As a wandering fortune teller, 
I will now head to a new destination,

00:04:37.540 --> 00:04:39.430
along with Meisho Doto.

00:04:40.230 --> 00:04:42.120
Oof...

00:04:40.480 --> 00:04:42.480
I doubt we will ever meet again.

00:04:42.480 --> 00:04:43.740
Come on.

00:04:43.510 --> 00:04:45.270
Please look after yourself...

00:04:43.740 --> 00:04:45.270
Okay...

00:04:45.270 --> 00:04:46.860
Machikane Fukukitaru.

00:04:49.900 --> 00:04:51.710
Fukukitaru-san!

00:04:53.470 --> 00:04:55.840
Helios... I'm gonna do my best.

00:04:55.840 --> 00:04:56.480
Yo...

00:04:56.870 --> 00:05:00.570
I'm sure Fukukitaru-san 
is watching, somewhere.

00:05:00.570 --> 00:05:01.340
Yo.

00:05:01.880 --> 00:05:04.280
All right, let's get to training!

00:05:03.280 --> 00:05:04.760
Hold it up, okay?

00:05:04.760 --> 00:05:05.380
Okay...

00:05:05.620 --> 00:05:06.760
Put your back into it!

00:05:06.760 --> 00:05:07.510
Like this?

00:05:07.510 --> 00:05:08.890
You're still here!

00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:11.080
It's the day of the Kikkashou,

00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:11.890
Kikkashou

00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:11.890
Kikkashou

00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:11.890
Kikkashou

00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:11.890
Kikkashou

00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:11.890
Kikkashou

00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:11.890
Kikkashou

00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:11.890
Kikkashou

00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:11.890
Kyoto Racecourse

00:05:11.080 --> 00:05:13.560
and here to witness a race to determine 
the strongest in a generation

00:05:13.560 --> 00:05:17.390
is a capacity crowd awaiting
 BNW's latest showdown.

00:05:17.930 --> 00:05:20.400
McQueen's doing more solo training, huh?

00:05:20.400 --> 00:05:23.790
We better keep a good eye on 
the others for her sake, then.

00:05:23.790 --> 00:05:24.280
Good point!

00:05:24.280 --> 00:05:28.150
She did a great job winning the Kyoto Daishoten,
 so I'm sure she's fine.

00:05:28.150 --> 00:05:29.120
Good point!

00:05:29.120 --> 00:05:30.780
The Kikkashou...

00:05:31.020 --> 00:05:32.410
Biwa Hayahide,

00:05:32.410 --> 00:05:33.790
Narita Taishin,

00:05:33.790 --> 00:05:35.540
and Winning Ticket.

00:05:35.780 --> 00:05:39.290
Which one of them is going 
to grab the last crown?

00:05:39.290 --> 00:05:43.960
They're all really strong. 
Let's scope them out for McQueen.

00:05:43.960 --> 00:05:44.950
Good idea.

00:05:59.790 --> 00:06:02.060
Miss, is something the matter?

00:06:02.480 --> 00:06:04.420
It's nothing!

00:06:15.370 --> 00:06:17.870
Past the fourth corner and 
entering the final straightaway,

00:06:17.870 --> 00:06:19.690
Biwa Hayahide's lead is only increasing!

00:06:19.690 --> 00:06:20.560
She's in first place!

00:06:20.560 --> 00:06:24.530
The only member of BNW yet to claim a crown 
looks like she's about to make her mark!

00:06:24.530 --> 00:06:27.630
On the outside, Arcade Champ and Winning Ticket
 are starting to move up!

00:06:27.630 --> 00:06:29.370
But Biwa Hayahide's lead is still growing!

00:06:29.370 --> 00:06:30.670
She's in first place!

00:06:30.670 --> 00:06:32.390
With a lead of four,

00:06:32.390 --> 00:06:33.350
now five lengths!

00:06:33.350 --> 00:06:34.700
The race for second place is hot!

00:06:34.700 --> 00:06:36.890
Winning Ticket </i>is doing her 
best to push forward!

00:06:36.890 --> 00:06:38.590
But look at that implacable lead!

00:06:38.590 --> 00:06:40.910
Biwa Hayahide with an unassailable 
show of strength!

00:06:40.910 --> 00:06:41.900
And she crosses the goal!

00:06:42.670 --> 00:06:44.900
The final race of the 
Classics, the Kikkashou,

00:06:44.900 --> 00:06:49.240
goes to the last member of 
BNW to win a race, Biwa Hayahide!

00:06:49.240 --> 00:06:50.940
With a five-length lead 
on the second-place finisher!

00:06:50.940 --> 00:06:55.380
She has won the G1 race said to be won 
by only the strongest horse girls!

00:06:55.830 --> 00:06:56.790
And this time...

00:06:56.790 --> 00:06:58.310
Record

00:06:56.790 --> 00:06:58.310
Record

00:06:56.790 --> 00:06:58.310
Record

00:06:56.790 --> 00:06:58.310
Record

00:06:56.790 --> 00:06:58.310
Record

00:06:56.790 --> 00:06:58.310
Record

00:06:56.790 --> 00:06:58.310
Record

00:06:57.020 --> 00:06:58.310
It's a record!

00:06:58.310 --> 00:06:59.790
She's broken the record

00:06:59.790 --> 00:07:01.110
set previously by Rice Shower!

00:07:02.100 --> 00:07:03.490
Wow...

00:07:04.040 --> 00:07:06.830
She blew them away. 
How does she run like that?

00:07:06.830 --> 00:07:07.910
Good question.

00:07:07.910 --> 00:07:09.800
She's got a lot of momentum.

00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:14.000
She stands out even among BNW.

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:17.180
She must've grown a bit over the summer.

00:07:18.940 --> 00:07:20.200
Nice run!

00:07:20.730 --> 00:07:21.840
Something wrong?

00:07:21.840 --> 00:07:22.440
Well...

00:07:22.650 --> 00:07:26.080
I could've sworn I just heard
someone say my head had grown too big.

00:07:26.080 --> 00:07:27.690
Really?

00:07:27.690 --> 00:07:31.450
Well, we saw the thing. 
Let's take our time on the way back.

00:07:31.770 --> 00:07:34.880
Since we're in Kyoto anyway, 
I wanna get some Nishin soba.

00:07:34.880 --> 00:07:35.510
Good point!

00:07:35.510 --> 00:07:36.660
In that case, I wanna matcha parfait!

00:07:36.660 --> 00:07:37.140
Good point!

00:07:37.140 --> 00:07:39.440
We can get both. And it 
can be Trainer's treat.

00:07:39.440 --> 00:07:40.330
Good point!

00:07:40.330 --> 00:07:42.800
Hold up! I didn't sign off on this!

00:07:43.620 --> 00:07:44.660
Maybe you're imagining things?

00:07:44.660 --> 00:07:47.920
No, I'm positive. 
Someone said my head was too big.

00:07:47.920 --> 00:07:49.340
But are you sure you're not imagining it?

00:07:49.340 --> 00:07:52.340
That can't be. Somebody had to have...

00:07:50.430 --> 00:07:52.340
You're imagining things!

00:07:52.340 --> 00:07:55.360
I know what I heard! Someone said it!

00:07:53.260 --> 00:07:54.610
Biwa Hayahide...

00:07:59.350 --> 00:08:00.350
Butler...

00:08:00.350 --> 00:08:01.080
Yes?

00:08:01.540 --> 00:08:03.840
Could you call the doctor?

00:08:03.840 --> 00:08:04.850
The family doctor?

00:08:04.850 --> 00:08:05.830
Yes.

00:08:05.830 --> 00:08:08.160
There's something I'd like him to look at.

00:08:08.160 --> 00:08:09.610
Miss...

00:08:09.610 --> 00:08:13.680
I'm sure it's nothing serious, 
but I'd like to take every precaution.

00:08:13.680 --> 00:08:15.650
Right. Understood.

00:08:15.650 --> 00:08:17.120
Here you are, miss.

00:08:23.100 --> 00:08:26.540
Honestly... I just said 
it was nothing serious.

00:08:36.460 --> 00:08:39.350
Everyone, let's eat some 
of that next! Come on!

00:08:39.590 --> 00:08:41.220
B-Bring it on...

00:08:41.220 --> 00:08:45.350
You still wanna eat? You're gonna wear 
down your stamina if you overdo it.

00:08:45.660 --> 00:08:48.690
You know what they say about autumn! 
Even horse girls get to enjoy harvest time.

00:08:48.690 --> 00:08:49.730
I guess...

00:08:49.730 --> 00:08:51.090
Me, too, then!

00:08:53.660 --> 00:08:54.360
What's up?

00:08:54.360 --> 00:08:56.940
Oh, I just wanted to pick 
something up for McQueen!

00:09:03.050 --> 00:09:04.270
What do you think?

00:09:05.670 --> 00:09:08.250
I'd like you to get bed rest 
for the time being.

00:09:11.500 --> 00:09:13.820
Maybe this? Or this?

00:09:13.820 --> 00:09:15.760
Or would she prefer this?

00:09:20.180 --> 00:09:23.030
This seems like an overreaction.

00:09:23.030 --> 00:09:27.020
Still, until we know the diagnosis,
 it's better to be safe than sorry.

00:09:28.470 --> 00:09:29.380
Come in.

00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:32.150
I'm the doctor.

00:09:32.150 --> 00:09:34.080
What did you learn, Doctor?

00:09:35.060 --> 00:09:36.330
Doctor?

00:09:36.330 --> 00:09:39.410
Miss, the lady of the house 
would like to speak to you.

00:09:41.630 --> 00:09:43.020
My grandmother?

00:09:46.770 --> 00:09:49.040
Heave-ho, heave-ho...

00:09:49.040 --> 00:09:50.420
And down.

00:09:52.200 --> 00:09:54.660
Man, nasty weather.

00:09:56.050 --> 00:09:57.140
Hey, Teio.

00:09:57.140 --> 00:09:58.900
Aw, it's just you, Trainer.

00:09:58.900 --> 00:10:01.050
Wow, rude. Is there a problem?

00:10:01.050 --> 00:10:03.100
No, I was just waiting for McQueen.

00:10:03.810 --> 00:10:05.890
I was hoping to give her these.

00:10:05.890 --> 00:10:08.810
Wait, today's the "best by" date!

00:10:06.830 --> 00:10:08.810
Coarse Red Sweet Bean-Filled Yatsuhashi
<font size="28">Kyoto's Finest Yatsuhashi, Nishino</font>

00:10:09.890 --> 00:10:11.210
Hey, where are you going?

00:10:11.210 --> 00:10:13.180
To deliver these to McQueen!

00:10:13.180 --> 00:10:15.190
I'll visit her while I'm at it!

00:10:15.190 --> 00:10:16.880
Back later!

00:10:17.940 --> 00:10:20.450
Honey, honey, honey!

00:10:20.450 --> 00:10:23.890
When I get a lick of that honey,

00:10:23.890 --> 00:10:29.640
I feel, feel, feel so much faster!

00:10:29.640 --> 00:10:32.190
Honey, honey, honey!

00:10:32.190 --> 00:10:35.210
When I get a lick of that honey...

00:10:35.480 --> 00:10:40.060
All right, this oughta cover 
the next training regimen.

00:10:42.590 --> 00:10:45.110
It's... McQueen's butler?

00:10:42.590 --> 00:10:45.110
Mr. Butler

00:10:47.520 --> 00:10:48.620
Hello?

00:10:48.620 --> 00:10:52.380
Man, this place is still intimidating.

00:10:52.380 --> 00:10:55.360
How do I even get inside?

00:10:55.760 --> 00:10:57.700
Pardon me.

00:10:59.730 --> 00:11:02.360
Honey, honey, honey!

00:11:02.360 --> 00:11:05.870
When I get a lick of that honey...

00:11:07.870 --> 00:11:09.620
Butler-san!

00:11:11.340 --> 00:11:13.410
Teio-sama, what brings you here?

00:11:13.410 --> 00:11:15.250
Sorry for coming in without permission.

00:11:15.250 --> 00:11:18.820
Is McQueen around? I came 
to visit her, and well...

00:11:18.820 --> 00:11:19.830
Well... er...

00:11:19.830 --> 00:11:20.880
Butler-san?

00:11:23.860 --> 00:11:27.390
I'm afraid Miss McQueen is not available.

00:11:27.390 --> 00:11:29.620
Oh, is she training? In that case...

00:11:29.620 --> 00:11:33.630
She is currently staying at 
the Mejiro family sanatorium.

00:11:36.770 --> 00:11:39.140
The sanatorium? Why?

00:11:39.140 --> 00:11:40.780
Did something happen to her?!

00:11:41.170 --> 00:11:44.790
An injury was discovered in her leg.

00:11:44.790 --> 00:11:45.660
What injury?

00:11:47.120 --> 00:11:51.540
The young miss has developed a case of 
suspensory ligament desmitis in her left leg.

00:11:53.050 --> 00:11:54.340
That's...

00:11:55.780 --> 00:11:58.910
It requires a year to treat,

00:11:58.910 --> 00:12:03.480
and even in the event of recovery, 
it is likely to reoccur.

00:12:04.270 --> 00:12:09.470
It's said to be one of the incurable 
conditions that can plague a horse girl.

00:12:12.710 --> 00:12:18.500
Unlike a fracture, it doesn't immediately 
prevent one from running. But...

00:12:18.500 --> 00:12:21.280
With each step, severe pain 
will afflict the affected area,

00:12:21.280 --> 00:12:24.240
with the worst case scenario being 
a permanent loss of mobility.

00:12:24.240 --> 00:12:25.640
So you see...

00:12:26.880 --> 00:12:30.650
Then McQueen can't run anymore?

00:12:31.750 --> 00:12:34.050
Racing would be terribly unwise.

00:12:34.550 --> 00:12:38.420
If she doesn't aggravate the injury, 
it shouldn't affect her everyday life.

00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:42.890
It's... what's best for her.

00:12:46.370 --> 00:12:47.510
Hello?

00:12:48.670 --> 00:12:50.010
She's missing?!

00:12:50.730 --> 00:12:53.520
No, I don't think she'd be that desperate.

00:12:53.520 --> 00:12:55.370
But then, I'm not sure where...

00:12:55.890 --> 00:12:57.160
Teio-sama?

00:12:58.190 --> 00:13:01.690
Coarse Red Sweet Bean-Filled Yatsuhashi
<font size="28">Kyoto's Finest Yatsuhashi, Nishino</font>

00:13:08.370 --> 00:13:09.700
McQueen!

00:13:12.990 --> 00:13:17.000
Umamusume

00:13:12.990 --> 00:13:17.000
{\an2}Pretty Derby

00:13:35.520 --> 00:13:38.730
See, it's fine. I'm still capable of running.

00:13:45.650 --> 00:13:47.740
Isn't this enough?

00:13:48.590 --> 00:13:51.130
You've accomplished so 
much while racing already,

00:13:51.130 --> 00:13:55.000
along with granting my wish 
of conquering the Tennoushou.

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:58.070
I could not be more proud of you.

00:13:59.230 --> 00:14:01.620
So, please, let's put an end to this.

00:14:01.620 --> 00:14:03.000
I cannot accept that!

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:05.130
I can still run!

00:14:05.130 --> 00:14:08.680
You can not. Your leg has reached its limit.

00:14:08.680 --> 00:14:12.470
That's how severe 
suspensory ligament desmitis is.

00:14:12.470 --> 00:14:14.300
I'm asking you to please listen to me—

00:14:14.300 --> 00:14:15.370
I refuse!

00:14:15.370 --> 00:14:17.390
I do not want to give up!

00:14:17.990 --> 00:14:19.250
Miss...

00:14:29.520 --> 00:14:33.920
That's right. I can hardly 
let this injury stop me.

00:14:35.630 --> 00:14:36.540
Because...

00:14:37.790 --> 00:14:39.820
I finally found her.

00:14:40.890 --> 00:14:42.750
I've finally encountered an opponent

00:14:43.150 --> 00:14:46.760
who I can clash with seriously, 
for the rest of my life.

00:14:47.510 --> 00:14:51.450
With you, I know I can run on forever.

00:14:52.260 --> 00:14:55.900
I knew it was our destiny on that day.

00:15:06.030 --> 00:15:09.460
Which is why... I can't let this stop me.

00:15:13.580 --> 00:15:15.840
Isn't it enough?

00:15:16.990 --> 00:15:18.790
An injury like this...

00:15:20.110 --> 00:15:21.980
is of no concern!

00:15:23.930 --> 00:15:29.670
Teio did it herself... time and time again, 
she rose to her feet and moved forward!

00:15:31.140 --> 00:15:33.890
After her dream of an undefeated 
triple crown was lost,

00:15:34.600 --> 00:15:36.300
after her dream of being 
undefeated was ended,

00:15:37.600 --> 00:15:39.320
after all the times she broke her leg...

00:15:40.680 --> 00:15:45.060
Miss, you've developed suspensory 
ligament desmitis in your left leg.

00:15:45.520 --> 00:15:49.320
I can still run! I'm Mejiro McQueen!

00:15:49.830 --> 00:15:54.710
And I will experience that moment, 
where we both give our all and run together,

00:15:54.710 --> 00:15:56.510
once more!

00:15:59.170 --> 00:16:04.000
This is an incurable condition for horse 
girls, with no effective treatment.

00:16:04.520 --> 00:16:07.110
I will run... again...

00:16:10.280 --> 00:16:12.550
I'm not gonna lose again!

00:16:12.840 --> 00:16:14.490
Challenge accepted.

00:16:17.170 --> 00:16:19.000
Isn't it enough?

00:16:19.790 --> 00:16:22.700
I promised her...

00:16:23.410 --> 00:16:29.520
From this moment on, I'd be glad 
to run so as to be a goal for you.

00:16:31.310 --> 00:16:34.330
I will run in a way that 
makes me fit to be your goal.

00:16:34.330 --> 00:16:35.540
Please, watch me.

00:16:36.190 --> 00:16:38.350
I will continue to run...

00:16:38.350 --> 00:16:41.290
So that I can remain the top horse girl.

00:16:41.650 --> 00:16:43.980
Your leg has reached its limit.

00:16:44.660 --> 00:16:47.590
I... want that again.

00:16:51.260 --> 00:16:53.110
To run with Teio...

00:17:05.910 --> 00:17:09.340
I... I...

00:17:11.480 --> 00:17:13.040
McQueen!

00:17:16.380 --> 00:17:17.470
Teio?

00:17:20.230 --> 00:17:21.620
McQueen!

00:17:23.920 --> 00:17:26.040
What's the matter, Teio?

00:17:26.540 --> 00:17:28.540
You're in such a panic.

00:17:29.470 --> 00:17:31.630
Butler-san told me...

00:17:31.630 --> 00:17:33.390
About your leg.

00:17:33.390 --> 00:17:35.300
Is that all?

00:17:35.300 --> 00:17:37.800
It won't be a problem at all.

00:17:38.220 --> 00:17:42.650
The Fall Tennoushou is in four days.
 I should resume training.

00:17:42.650 --> 00:17:44.450
But it has to hurt a lot, right?

00:17:44.450 --> 00:17:49.670
I can still manage to run. 
I'll simply have to bear with the pain.

00:17:50.390 --> 00:17:52.690
This won't be enough to...

00:17:54.970 --> 00:17:56.230
Don't force yourself!

00:17:56.230 --> 00:17:57.670
I am not!

00:17:58.550 --> 00:17:59.960
McQueen...

00:17:59.960 --> 00:18:03.400
I must... remain strong!

00:18:04.640 --> 00:18:06.690
With dignity, never giving an inch...

00:18:07.230 --> 00:18:10.570
I have to remain in the position 
of the strongest horse girl.

00:18:11.460 --> 00:18:14.960
That's where I will wait for you.

00:18:15.470 --> 00:18:17.450
I've looked forward to it for so long...

00:18:21.310 --> 00:18:23.700
We can compete to see who is the—

00:18:34.810 --> 00:18:35.780
But...

00:18:37.010 --> 00:18:40.360
It won't move. I can't make it move...

00:18:43.620 --> 00:18:47.050
I... can't run anymore.

00:18:49.140 --> 00:18:53.770
I can't keep my promise to you!

00:19:30.630 --> 00:19:33.380
Fate's kind of a jerk, huh?

00:19:35.250 --> 00:19:38.730
It really seems set on keeping 
us from racing each other.

00:19:42.930 --> 00:19:47.960
I thought we'd be able to run again at the 
Takarazuka Kinen... then I broke my leg.

00:19:48.670 --> 00:19:51.940
People started saying I wouldn't be 
able to run the same way again.

00:19:52.440 --> 00:19:54.740
And now, this happens to you.

00:19:56.390 --> 00:20:00.470
It'd probably be easier to just give up, huh?

00:20:00.470 --> 00:20:03.860
But... I don't want to give up yet.

00:20:03.860 --> 00:20:05.820
I want to run with you again.

00:20:08.470 --> 00:20:10.330
Don't you feel the same way?

00:20:10.970 --> 00:20:16.680
Of course I want to run! But I can't anymore!

00:20:16.680 --> 00:20:19.460
I may never be able to run again!

00:20:19.830 --> 00:20:23.970
Unless a miracle happens, I'll never 
be able to run like I used to!

00:20:24.260 --> 00:20:26.060
Just like you!

00:20:29.710 --> 00:20:31.800
F-Forgive me...

00:20:32.550 --> 00:20:36.620
No, you're right. Without a miracle,
 it's not gonna happen.

00:20:37.150 --> 00:20:39.480
So it's time to make a miracle.

00:20:40.590 --> 00:20:46.620
I'm going to prove that you 
and I can run together again.

00:20:47.900 --> 00:20:53.260
Watch the Arima Kinen, okay? I'm gonna 
cross that goal before anybody else.

00:20:56.910 --> 00:21:01.780
Y-You can't possibly win... 
not in the condition you're in.

00:21:01.780 --> 00:21:03.680
I'm going to win anyway.

00:21:04.880 --> 00:21:08.140
If I work hard enough to make a 
miracle happen, I know I can do it.

00:21:12.530 --> 00:21:17.260
Miracles can happen when people 
wish and strive for them.

00:21:17.650 --> 00:21:19.760
I'm sure of that.

00:21:24.390 --> 00:21:25.600
Teio...

00:21:26.980 --> 00:21:31.010
When I was on the verge of giving up,
 you pulled me forward.

00:21:31.830 --> 00:21:35.050
When I felt like I was going 
to break, you were by my side.

00:21:36.700 --> 00:21:40.540
You've been the kind of strong 
horse girl I could chase after.

00:21:41.870 --> 00:21:44.450
You were the one who said 
you'd wait for me.

00:21:46.410 --> 00:21:48.220
And now, it's my turn.

00:21:49.710 --> 00:21:52.180
So watch me, McQueen.

00:21:53.610 --> 00:21:54.890
Teio...

00:22:18.020 --> 00:22:18.770
Miss!

00:22:18.770 --> 00:22:20.710
Miss, you're soaked!

